Impacts 7

Case 1: Optimize Patient Satisfaction by Reducing Wait Times

Improving wait times, particularly in Emergency and Outpatient services, has significantly boosted patient satisfaction. By focusing on reducing wait times and implementing cultural competence training, satisfaction rates have increased, particularly among Asian patients. This proactive approach not only enhances patient experience but also builds trust and encourages faster diagnoses, leading to overall higher satisfaction levels.

Case 2: Enhance Service Quality for Older Patients

Addressing the specific needs of older patients (aged 70+) has proven effective in raising satisfaction levels. By focusing on reducing wait times, improving communication, and offering personalized care, satisfaction among older patients has improved. This approach not only benefits the patients by providing better care but also strengthens the healthcare providerâ€™s reputation and encourages patient loyalty.
